\section{Graphics}
\PAWPP{} allows direct graphics manipulation of the objects like Histograms
or Ntuples. To perform actions on object from the \GW, it is
enough to move the mouse cursor on the \GW{} and to click with the
right mouse button on the object. A pull down menu will be displayed according
to the object picked. In this section are described the different menus
available in the \GW.

\MENU{graphics}

\newpage

\subsection{The \GW}
When no object is picked in the \GW{} for instance when the
background of the window is picked the following menu is displayed.

\begin{PAWf}[.4]{graphicswindow}
\begin{DLsf}{Do Encapsulated PostScript...}
\item[Plot]                           \Lit{ Picture/Plot}
\item[Style Panel...]                 \Lit{ show_histoStyle}
\item[Double Buffer On]               \Lit{ Igset 2BUF 1}
\item[Double Buffer Off]              \Lit{ Igset 2BUF 0}
\item[Do PostScript...]               \Lit{ -Picture/Print paw.ps}
\item[Do Encapsulated PostScript...]  \Lit{ -Picture/Print paw.eps}
\item[Do LaTex...]                    \Lit{ -Picture/Print paw.tex}
\item[Print]                          \Lit{ Picture/Print}
\item[Open New Window]                \Lit{ Work [this] OA}
\item[Close Window]                   \Lit{ Work [this] C}
\item[Activate Window]                \Lit{ Work [this] A}
\item[Deactivate Window]              \Lit{ Work [this] D}
\end{DLsf}
\end{PAWf}


\subsection{Ntuple}
When a Ntuple is picked in \GW{} with the right mouse button,
the following menu is displayed:

\begin{PAWf}{graphicsntuple}
\begin{DLsf}{Open Ntuple Viewer}
\item[Open Ntuple Viewer]     \Lit{ default_action}
\item[Project...]             \Lit{ Ntuple/Proj IDN=[this]}
\item[Print]                  \Lit{ Ntuple/Print [this]}
\end{DLsf}
\end{PAWf}

\newpage

\subsection{1D-Histogram}
When a 1D-Histogram is picked in \GW{} with the right mouse button,
the following menu is displayed:

\begin{PAWf}{graphics1d}
\begin{DLsf}{Filled Lego}
\item[Fit...]                   \Lit{Histo/Fit [this]}
\item[Fit Gauss]                \Lit{Histo/Fit [this] G}
\item[Fit Exp]                  \Lit{Histo/Fit [this] E}
\item[Fit Const]                \Lit{Histo/Fit [this] P0}
\item[Fit Linear]               \Lit{Histo/Fit [this] P1}
\item[Smooth]                   \Lit{Smooth [this]}
\item[Smooth...]                \Lit{Smooth [this]}
\item[Line]                     \Lit{Histo/Plot [this] L}
\item[Curve]                    \Lit{Histo/Plot [this] C}
\item[Bar Chart]                \Lit{Histo/Plot [this] B}
\item[Marker]                   \Lit{Histo/Plot [this] P}
\item[Stars]                    \Lit{Histo/Plot [this] *}
\item[Error Bars]               \Lit{Histo/Plot [this] E}
\item[Error Bars (lines)]       \Lit{Histo/Plot [this] E1}
\item[Error Rectangles]         \Lit{Histo/Plot [this] E2}
\item[Error: Filled Area]       \Lit{Histo/Plot [this] E3}
\item[Error: Smoothed Area]     \Lit{Histo/Plot [this] E4}
\item[Lego]                     \Lit{Histo/Plot [this] LEGO}
\item[Filled Lego]              \Lit{Histo/Plot [this] LEGO1}
\item[Default]                  \Lit{Histo/Plot [this]}
\end{DLsf}
\end{PAWf}

\newpage

\subsection{2D-Histogram}
When a 2D-Histogram is picked in \GW{} with the right mouse button,
the following menu is displayed:

\begin{PAWf}[.33]{graphics2d}
\begin{DLsf}{Color Level Surface (1)}
\item[Project X]       \Lit{ProX [this]; Hi/Proj [this]; Hi/Plot [this].proX}
\item[Project Y]       \Lit{ProY [this]; Hi/Proj [this]; Hi/Plot [this].proY}
\item[Slice X]         \Lit{SliX [this]; Hi/Proj [this]; Hi/Plot [this].sliX.1}
\item[Slice Y]         \Lit{SliY [this]; Hi/Proj [this]; Hi/Plot [this].sliY.1}
\item[Band X]          \Lit{BanX [this]; Hi/Proj [this]; Hi/Plot [this].banX.1}
\item[Band Y]          \Lit{BanY [this]; Hi/Proj [this]; Hi/Plot [this].banY.1}
\item[Smooth]                  \Lit{Smooth [this]}
\item[Smooth...]               \Lit{Smooth [this]}
\item[Boxes]                   \Lit{Histo/Plot [this] BOX}
\item[Color]                   \Lit{Histo/Plot [this] COLZ}
\item[Hidden Lines Surface]    \Lit{Histo/Plot [this] SURF}
\item[Color Level Surface (1)] \Lit{Histo/Plot [this] SURF1}
\item[Color Level Surface (2)] \Lit{Histo/Plot [this] SURF2}
\item[Surface and Contour]     \Lit{Histo/Plot [this] SURF3}
\item[Gouraud Shaded Surface]  \Lit{Histo/Plot [this] SURF4}
\item[Hidden Lines Lego]       \Lit{Histo/Plot [this] LEGO}
\item[Filled Lego]             \Lit{Histo/Plot [this] LEGO1}
\item[Color Level Lego]        \Lit{Histo/Plot [this] LEGO2}
\item[Contour Plot]            \Lit{Histo/Plot [this] CONT}
\item[Filled Contour Plot]     \Lit{Set NCOl 28;Pal 1;Conto [this] 20 3}
\item[Arrow Plot]              \Lit{Histo/Plot [this] ARR}
\item[Text]                    \Lit{Histo/Plot [this] TEXT}
\item[Default]                 \Lit{Histo/Plot [this] SCAT}
\end{DLsf}
\end{PAWf}

